@startuml Diagramme de Déploiement - Architecture

title Diagramme de Déploiement\nArchitecture du Système

node "Poste Client" as Client {
  component "Navigateur Web\n(Chrome, Firefox)" as Browser {
    artifact "index.html"
    artifact "login.html"
    artifact "register.html"
    artifact "declaration.html"
    artifact "recherche.html"
    artifact "dashboard.html"
    artifact "script.js"
    artifact "style.css"
  }
}

node "Serveur Application" as AppServer {
  component "Node.js Runtime" as NodeJS {
    artifact "server.js\n(API REST Express)"
    artifact "intelligent-search.js\n(Algorithme fuzzy)"
    artifact "hash-passwords.js"
  }

  component "Bibliothèques" as Libs {
    artifact "express\n(Framework web)"
    artifact "bcrypt\n(Hachage MDP)"
    artifact "jsonwebtoken\n(JWT Auth)"
    artifact "fuse.js\n(Fuzzy search)"
    artifact "string-similarity\n(Levenshtein)"
    artifact "cors\n(CORS support)"
    artifact "dotenv\n(Variables env)"
  }
}

node "Stockage Données" as Storage {
  database "JSON Files" as DB {
    artifact "users.json\n(Utilisateurs)"
    artifact "documents.json\n(Documents)"
  }

  artifact ".env\n(Secrets)"
}

node "CDN Externe" as CDN {
  artifact "Chart.js\n(Graphiques)"
}

' Relations
Browser -down-> NodeJS : HTTP/HTTPS\nRequêtes API REST\nJSON + JWT Token
NodeJS -down-> DB : Lecture/Écriture\nJSON
NodeJS .left.> Libs : utilise
NodeJS .down.> ".env" : charge
Browser .up.> CDN : charge\nChart.js

' Notes
note right of Browser
  **Frontend**
  - HTML5 + CSS3
  - JavaScript Vanilla
  - LocalStorage (token JWT)
  - Fetch API (HTTP)
end note

note right of NodeJS
  **Backend**
  - Node.js + Express
  - Architecture REST
  - Authentification JWT
  - Algorithmes intelligents
  - Middleware sécurisé
end note

note right of DB
  **Persistance**
  - Format JSON
  - Lecture/écriture synchrone
  - Extensible vers PostgreSQL
  - Fichiers versionnés (Git)
end note

note bottom
  **Protocole HTTP/HTTPS**
  - GET /recherche (protégée)
  - POST /declaration (protégée)
  - GET /correspondances (protégée)
  - GET /statistiques (admin)
  - POST /login (publique)
  - POST /register (publique)

  **Token JWT** dans header:
  Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOi...
end note

@enduml
